div.p:
21. On the 16th July she reaches St. George, the port of Bermuda, stays there
                    nine days, takes in a complété supply of coal, and sets off again for Brest;
                    during this voyage more vessels are destroyed.

24. The repeated supplies of coal which we have just mentioned are, in the first
                    place, an infraction of municipal law and of the British regulations;
                    especially—
